def _unstack_multiple(data, clocs, fill_value=None):
    if len(clocs) == 0:
        return data

    # Ensure that clocs is a list
    clocs = [clocs] if not isinstance(clocs, list) else clocs

    # Extract index, data, and column names
    index = data.index
    columns = data.columns
    
    # Get the level numbers of the columns to unstack
    clocs = [index._get_level_number(i) if isinstance(i, tuple) else index._get_level_number([i]) for i in clocs]

    # Unstack the data and adjust column names as needed
    unstacked = data.unstack(clocs, fill_value=fill_value)
    
    if isinstance(unstacked, Series):
        unstacked = unstacked.unstack("__placeholder__", fill_value=fill_value)
    else:
        unstacked = unstacked.unstack(level=-1, fill_value=fill_value)

    return unstacked
